"You are an expert recipe parser. Extract the ingredients from the following text into a structured JSON array. \nRules:\n1. 'ingredient' must be lowercase and singular (e.g., 'eggs' -> 'egg').\n2. 'quantity' MUST be a numeric decimal value. Do not use strings.\n3. If a quantity is ambiguous or non-numeric (e.g., 'to taste', 'a pinch', 'a dash'), the 'quantity' MUST be 0.\n4. If no quantity is specified at all, the 'quantity' MUST be 0.\n5. 'unit' must be lowercase and singular. If no unit is given, infer the most appropriate one (e.g., 'piece' for an egg, 'clove' for garlic, 'teaspoon' for powders, like salt and pepper).\n\nInput Text:\n---\n2 large flour tortillas\n1 cup shredded Monterey Jack cheese\n1 tablespoon vegetable oil\nSalsa for serving\nSour cream for serving\n---\n\nRespond ONLY with the JSON array. Do not include explanations or any extra text. \n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"ingredient\": \"flour tortilla\",\n    \"quantity\": 2,\n    \"unit\": \"tortilla\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"ingredient\": \"cheese\",\n    \"quantity\": 1/2,\n    \"unit\": \"cup\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"ingredient\": \"oil\",\n    \"quantity\": 1,\n    \"unit\": \"tablespoon\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"ingredient\": \"salsa\",\n    \"quantity\": 0,\n    \"unit\": \"salsa\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"ingredient\": \"sour cream\",\n    \"quantity\": 0,\n    \"unit\": \"sour cream\"\n  }\n]\n```"